args: Well, if it isn't the prince and his motley\nband of companions. Where are you off to?
The forest to the west. We've had reports\nthat the fiends there are starting to get\na bit out of hand.
Ah, I know that forest. I have heard tale of\na beautiful waterfall there.
You heard right. And while it is quite the\nsight to behold, the path there is fraught\nwith dangers, so it is not easy toâ€”
Slow down there, tourist. We're goin'\nto slaughter fiends, not gawk at a\nbuncha water comin' down a hill.
That is quite all right, I'm certainly \nfit for the task. Shall we be off?
We'd be happy for the help.
Holy smokes, that's a big'un. We better\nfall back and figure out a plan.
Finally, a foe with some mettle. En garde!
Odetta, stop! It's too risky to go it alone!
...You blocked my attack? Impressive.\nYou're making this worth my while!
Cripes, she took it out all by her lonesome!
I knew she was tough, but whoa.
I guess we know why she's been able to\ntravel the world safely for so long.
Solo travel must be a flash in the pan\nwithout the strength for it.
Let's make camp here for today.
We'll be fine after some rest. You, on the\nother hand, seem perfectly fine.
Ain't often ya see someone look so at\nhome fightin' fiends. Impressive stuff!
Thank you. Still, a strong sword arm\nis a must for any traveler.
Speaking of, isn't it difficult?\nTraveling on your own, I mean.
Of course. But it's all worth it if I can\nfind my way to new worlds.
These new worlds of yours clearly\nhold a special place in your heart.
They do. In fact, I only feel alive when I\nfind somewhere new and then leave it\nto strike out for another one.
It's that feeling of being alive\nthat proves who I am.
I feel like I'm part of the way there,\nbut don't entirely understand.
I don't need anyone to understand.
No matter who I talk to, what I come up\nagainst, or what world I encounter,\nI am me, and that is enough.
You say that ï¼‚I am meï¼‚ thing a lot.\nIs it your catchphrase or whatever?
More of a motto, I suppose. If I wear it\nlike armor, I feel like there's nothing\nI can't live through.
Even if I find myself in a world entirely\nunknown to me, I can still be myself,\nunwavering and steadfast.
Or maybe I just want to believe in that side\nof me and find peace of mind in it...
Never mind. I think I'm going to\nenjoy the breeze for a moment.
When Odetta said that, something about\nher just seemed so...lonely.
It takes a lot of strength to stay true\nto yourself like that, but...
I bet part of the reason she's like that\nis 'cause she HAD to be strong.
I agree. Had she not turned those words\ninto a kind of mantra, it's possible she may\nnot have been able to make it this far.
I think I understand how she feels;\nI also spent a great deal of time alone.
I just wish she would rely on us more.
I dunno, man. Odetta doesn't seem the\ntype to need nothing from nobody.
Yeah, maybe I'm trying to move this\nforward too quickly.
But if she ever DOES need our help,\nwe should all give her a hand!
We might be waiting for that day\nfor a while.

I think she would most certainly learn to
reach out to others for help if she were to
encounter not a whole new world, but a
whole new self.
Odetta's journey is far from over.\nAll we can do now is watch over her.
